column11: KATOLICKI UNIWERSYTET LUBELSKI JANA PAWLA II
column44: Students are considered in priority for DEUF (french) programme, and might be considered for SELF (english) programme if they show an insufficient level in french but good english speaking abilities. DEUF program: minimum B1 level in French. Students are allowed to take courses in various faculties. A French language certificate will be sent to the coordinator prior nominations that he/she will have to fill out and precise the student&#039.s level in French (B1 in Buisness) SELF program: maximum A2 level in French. Students follow courses in English only For students enrolled in a university where English is not the official language, one of the official tests listed below is required: - TOEFL IBT: overall score of 80 or higher with 20 at least for each section – only the official test will accepted (the local version is not adequate) - TOEFL ITP: overall score of 560 minimum and no section score below 50 - IELTS Academic: overall score of 6,5 and no section score below 6 - TOEIC including speaking, writing, listening and reading test: overall score of 1020 - Cambridge Advanced: A/B - Cambridge Proficiency: C minimum The English test has to be provided upon nomination (end of April for the fall semester and end of October for the spring semester). Two courses in common for these programs: - FLE (French as a foreign language) - Introduction to French culture

SELF program: maximum A2 level in French. column44: KUL will accept Social Work students from ASH. At KUL they will be registered in the Pedagogy/Education degree programme and must take at least one course from this programme. In addition, they will be free to choose courses from other fields of study too, be it from English-taught programmes or Polish ones (provided they know Polish).

column44: Please note that: the number of students each institution will send may by no means exceed the number of students mentioned in this agreement. More specifically shorter periods of stay do not allow for the sending of more students, i.e. on an exchange of 1 student for 10 months, a partner cannot send 2 students for 5 months, not even if their stay covers different semesters. The numbers of months per student the partners have agreed on are fixed. An extension of stay is only possible, when e. g. a student is nominated for 5 months, but the partners have agreed on an exchange of 1 student for 10 months. Students should apply early in advance for an extension of stay, at least one month before the regular stay ends.  A written aAcceptance of both partners (incl. International Office) is mandatory and should not exceed the number of months agreed per students. Each party will take this into consideration when organizing student selection.
